<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> Operation Overlord planned for an advance to the line of the Seine by D+90 and an advance to the German frontier some time after D+120.</li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> Danny Parker, <i>The Battle of the Bulge</i>, pp.95–100; Samuel Mitcham, <i>Panzers in Winter</i>, p.38; Steven Newton, <i>Hitler’s Commander</i>, pp.329–334. <i>Wacht am Rhein</i> was renamed <i>Herbstnebel</i> after the operation was given the go-ahead in early December, although its original name remains much better known.</li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Major Kevin Dougherty, <a href="http://www.fas.org/irp/agency/army/mipb/2002_04.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.fas.org/irp/agency/army/mipb/2002_04.pdf" rel="nofollow">'Oscar Koch: An Unsung Hero Behind Patton's Victories'</a>, <i>Military Intelligence Professional Bulletin April-June 2002</i>, pp. 64-66</li>
